P.append(passage("j8_observe_006",
    "The Patience of Repair Shops", "修理铺的耐心", 8,
    "在我住的那条老街上，有一家修伞铺、一家修鞋铺和一家修钟表的小店。它们夹在奶茶店和快递驿站之间，显得格外突兀，像三个从另一个时代穿越来的幸存者。修伞的老周每天上午九点准时开门，在一张磨得发亮的木桌前坐下，戴上老花镜，等待顾客。他有时一整个上午都没有生意，就坐在那里磨伞骨上的锈迹，那种专注的神情像极了外科医生。我问他为什么不转行做更赚钱的生意，他想了想说：「这条街上已经没有人会修伞了，我要是也不修了，大家就只能扔掉再买新的。」这句话听起来平淡，却包含了一种朴素的伦理观：修复比替代更有尊严。修鞋的陈师傅说得更直接：「一双好鞋，修修补补能穿十年。现在的人买鞋跟买菜似的，穿一季就扔。」钟表铺的刘阿姨则几乎从不说话，她用一把小得不可思议的螺丝刀在表盘内部操作，偶尔会把某个零件举到灯下端详很久。这三家店的共同之处在于：它们都在对抗一种叫做「一次性文化」的潮流，用一种近乎固执的耐心。",
    "Zài wǒ zhù de nà tiáo lǎojiē shàng, yǒu yī jiā xiū sǎn pù, yī jiā xiū xié pù hé yī jiā xiū zhōngbiǎo de xiǎo diàn. Tāmen jiā zài nǎichá diàn hé kuàidì yìzhàn zhījiān, xiǎn de géwài tūwù, xiàng sān gè cóng lìng yī gè shídài chuānyuè lái de xìngcúnzhě. Xiū sǎn de lǎo Zhōu měi tiān shàngwǔ jiǔ diǎn zhǔnshí kāimén, zài yī zhāng mó de fāliàng de mùzhuō qián zuò xià, dài shàng lǎohuā jìng, děngdài gùkè. Tā yǒushí yī zhěnggè shàngwǔ dōu méiyǒu shēngyì, jiù zuò zài nàlǐ mó sǎngǔ shàng de xiùjì, nà zhǒng zhuānzhù de shénqíng xiàng jí le wàikē yīshēng. Wǒ wèn tā wèishéme bù zhuǎnháng zuò gèng zhuànqián de shēngyì, tā xiǎng le xiǎng shuō: zhè tiáo jiē shàng yǐjīng méiyǒu rén huì xiū sǎn le, wǒ yàoshi yě bù xiū le, dàjiā jiù zhǐ néng rēngdiào zài mǎi xīn de. Zhè jù huà tīng qǐlái píngdàn, què bāohán le yī zhǒng pǔsù de lúnlǐguān: xiūfù bǐ tìdài gèng yǒu zūnyán.",
    "On the old street where I live, there is an umbrella repair shop, a shoe repair shop, and a small watch repair store. Wedged between a milk tea shop and a courier station, they look strikingly out of place, like three survivors from another era. Old Zhou the umbrella mender opens at nine each morning, sits at a wooden table polished smooth by years of use, puts on reading glasses, and waits. Sometimes he has no business all morning, so he scrubs rust off umbrella ribs with the focus of a surgeon. I asked him why he doesn't switch to something more profitable. He thought and said: 'Nobody on this street can fix umbrellas anymore. If I stop too, people can only throw them away and buy new ones.' The words sound plain but contain a simple ethics: repair has more dignity than replacement. Cobbler Chen is more direct: 'A good pair of shoes, patched up, can last ten years. People nowadays buy shoes like vegetables—wear them one season and toss them.' Auntie Liu at the watch shop almost never speaks. She works inside watch faces with an impossibly small screwdriver, occasionally lifting a part to the lamplight to study it. What these three shops share: they all resist a trend called disposable culture, with a patience bordering on stubbornness.",
    mc("老周坚持修伞的核心理由是什么？",
       "What is Old Zhou's core reason for continuing to repair umbrellas?",
       [o("修伞利润比看起来高","xiū sǎn lìrùn bǐ kàn qǐlái gāo","Umbrella repair is more profitable than it looks"),
        o("如果他也停了，这项技能在街区就彻底消失了","rúguǒ tā yě tíng le, zhè xiàng jìnéng zài jiēqū jiù chèdǐ xiāoshī le","If he stops too, this skill will vanish from the neighborhood",True),
        o("他年纪大了无法学习新技能","tā niánjì dà le wúfǎ xuéxí xīn jìnéng","He's too old to learn new skills"),
        o("房东给他的租金很便宜","fángdōng gěi tā de zūjīn hěn piányí","His landlord charges low rent")], 0.4),
    mc("作者用「外科医生」来形容老周，最主要想表达什么？",
       "What does comparing Old Zhou to a 'surgeon' primarily express?",
       [o("修伞和外科手术一样复杂","xiū sǎn hé wàikē shǒushù yīyàng fùzá","Umbrella repair is as complex as surgery"),
        o("老周对修理工作投入了与医生同等级的专注和尊重","lǎo Zhōu duì xiūlǐ gōngzuò tóurù le yǔ yīshēng tóng děngjí de zhuānzhù hé zūnzhòng","Old Zhou brings a surgeon's level of focus and respect to his work",True),
        o("老周曾经是一名医生","lǎo Zhōu céngjīng shì yī míng yīshēng","Old Zhou was once a doctor"),
        o("修伞需要精密的工具","xiū sǎn xūyào jīngmì de gōngjù","Umbrella repair requires precision tools")], 0.45),
    mc("文章认为「修复比替代更有尊严」，这里的「尊严」指的是什么？",
       "What does 'dignity' mean when the article says 'repair has more dignity than replacement'?",
       [o("修理工人的社会地位","xiūlǐ gōngrén de shèhuì dìwèi","The social status of repair workers"),
        o("对物品价值和人类劳动的尊重","duì wùpǐn jiàzhí hé rénlèi láodòng de zūnzhòng","Respect for the value of objects and human labor",True),
        o("手工艺品比工业品更贵","shǒugōngyì pǐn bǐ gōngyè pǐn gèng guì","Handicrafts are more expensive"),
        o("旧东西比新东西更好用","jiù dōngxi bǐ xīn dōngxi gèng hǎo yòng","Old things work better than new ones")], 0.5)))

# 5 - inst
P.append(passage("j8_inst_001",
    "The Unwritten Rules of the Public Library", "公共图书馆的潜规则", 8,
    "公共图书馆是一个由无数不成文规则维持秩序的空间。没有任何一块告示牌会告诉你：自习室里最靠窗的那排座位属于考研的学生，他们从早上开馆就来占座，桌上堆满了颜色各异的参考书和保温杯；中间几排是退休老人的领地，他们看报纸，偶尔小声交谈，享受的不是阅读本身而是一种公共空间的陪伴感；最后两排靠近电源插座的位置则被自由职业者和远程工作者默默瓜分，他们的标志性配置是笔记本电脑加一副耳机。这套座位分配系统从未被明文规定，却运行得异常稳定。偶尔有不知情的新来者坐错位置，会收到周围人微妙的目光提示——不是敌意，而是一种温和的纠偏信号。我在这座图书馆观察了两年，发现这套系统的核心逻辑是：人们根据自己对时间的使用方式来选择座位。考研学生需要专注所以选择窗边的光线，老人需要社交所以选择中间区域，远程工作者需要电源所以选择后排。当一个空间允许人们自发地形成秩序，而不是用规章制度去规定秩序，这个空间就获得了一种有机的生命力。",
    "Gōnggòng túshūguǎn shì yī gè yóu wúshù bù chéngwén guīzé wéichí zhìxù de kōngjiān. Méiyǒu rènhé yī kuài gàoshìpái huì gàosu nǐ: zìxíshì lǐ zuì kào chuāng de nà pái zuòwèi shǔyú kǎoyán de xuéshēng, tāmen cóng zǎoshang kāiguǎn jiù lái zhàn zuò, zhuō shàng duī mǎn le yánsè gè yì de cānkǎoshū hé bǎowēnbēi; zhōngjiān jǐ pái shì tuìxiū lǎorén de lǐngdì, tāmen kàn bàozhǐ, ǒu'ěr xiǎoshēng jiāotán, xiǎngshòu de bú shì yuèdú běnshēn ér shì yī zhǒng gōnggòng kōngjiān de péibàngǎn; zuìhòu liǎng pái kàojìn diànyuán chāzuò de wèizhì zé bèi zìyóu zhíyèzhě hé yuǎnchéng gōngzuòzhě mòmò guāfēn, tāmen de biāozhìxìng pèizhì shì bǐjìběn diànnǎo jiā yī fù ěrjī. Zhè tào zuòwèi fēnpèi xìtǒng cóng wèi bèi míngwén guīdìng, què yùnxíng de yìcháng wěndìng.",
    "A public library is a space maintained by countless unwritten rules. No sign tells you that window-side seats in the study room belong to graduate exam students, who arrive at opening to claim spots with colorful reference books and thermos cups; the middle rows are retirees' territory, who read newspapers and occasionally chat softly, enjoying not reading itself but a sense of companionship in public space; the last two rows near outlets are silently divided among freelancers and remote workers, whose signature setup is a laptop plus headphones. This seating system has never been formally established yet runs remarkably stably. When a newcomer sits in the wrong spot, they receive subtle glances—not hostile, but a gentle corrective signal. I observed this library for two years and found the core logic: people choose seats based on how they use time. Exam students need focus and choose window light, retirees need social contact and choose the middle, remote workers need power and choose the back. When a space allows people to spontaneously form order rather than imposing it through regulations, that space acquires organic vitality.",
    mc("作者认为图书馆座位分配系统的核心逻辑是什么？",
       "What is the core logic of the library seating system?",
       [o("先到先得的竞争原则","xiān dào xiān dé de jìngzhēng yuánzé","First-come-first-served competition"),
        o("人们根据自己使用时间的方式选择座位","rénmen gēnjù zìjǐ shǐyòng shíjiān de fāngshì xuǎnzé zuòwèi","People choose seats based on how they use time",True),
        o("图书馆管理员的暗中安排","túshūguǎn guǎnlǐyuán de ànzhōng ānpái","Secret arrangements by the librarian"),
        o("年龄和社会地位的等级制度","niánlíng hé shèhuì dìwèi de děngjí zhìdù","A hierarchy of age and social status")], 0.4),
    mc("退休老人选择中间区域的根本原因是什么？",
       "Why do retirees fundamentally choose the middle area?",
       [o("中间区域光线最好","zhōngjiān qūyù guāngxiàn zuì hǎo","The middle has the best lighting"),
        o("他们来图书馆是为了享受公共陪伴感","tāmen lái túshūguǎn shì wèile xiǎngshòu gōnggòng péibàngǎn","They come for a sense of public companionship",True),
        o("中间座位最舒服","zhōngjiān zuòwèi zuì shūfu","Middle seats are most comfortable"),
        o("其他座位已经被占了","qítā zuòwèi yǐjīng bèi zhàn le","Other seats are already taken")], 0.4),
    mc("作者对这种自发形成的秩序持什么态度？",
       "What is the author's attitude toward this spontaneous order?",
       [o("认为它效率低下，应该用规章替代","rènwéi tā xiàolǜ dīxià, yīnggāi yòng guīzhāng tìdài","Considers it inefficient, should be replaced by regulations"),
        o("欣赏它赋予空间的有机生命力","xīnshǎng tā fùyǔ kōngjiān de yǒujī shēngmìnglì","Appreciates the organic vitality it gives the space",True),
        o("担忧它会导致冲突","dānyōu tā huì dǎozhì chōngtū","Worries it will lead to conflicts"),
        o("认为它只是巧合，没有深层含义","rènwéi tā zhǐshì qiǎohé, méiyǒu shēncéng hányì","Considers it mere coincidence")], 0.4)))

